<div class="section">
  <h3>ABSTRACT</h3>
  <p>
    In Hong Kong, teachers and students face growing challenges in assessment scale, turnaround time, and personalized feedback. Traditional assessment workflows (manual marking, static question banks) struggle to support large cohorts and continuous practice. Therefore, our project provides an AI-driven solution that accelerates grading, expands high-quality question generation, and forms a closed loop from practice to analytics.
  </p>
  <p>
    Our project implements an end-to-end web platform that integrates:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>AI scoring for fill-in-the-blank and programming questions with robust fallback to rule-based marking.</li>
    <li>AI question generation by subject/topic/difficulty/type.</li>
    <li>Practice papers, tasks, exams, wrong-question drills, and CSV import/export pipelines.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Users (Admin/Teacher/Student) can manage subjects and questions, generate papers, practice, submit answers, receive AI feedback, and export logs. The main purpose is to increase assessment efficiency and feedback quality with measurable stability and usability improvements.
  </p>
</div>

