<div class="section">
  <h3>1. Introduction</h3>
  <h4>1.1 Overview</h4>
  <p>
    This project delivers a modern assessment platform combining:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Frontend: Vue 3 + Vue Router + Vuex + View UI Plus</li>
    <li>Backend: Django (RESTful APIs)</li>
    <li>Database: MySQL</li>
    <li>AI: OpenAI/OpenRouter (through a unified AI utility)</li>
    <li>Features: AI scoring, AI question generation, practice papers, tasks, exams, wrong-question practice, CSV import/export, role-based menus</li>
  </ul>
  <p>The system targets scalability, faster marking, and better learning experience.</p>
  <h4>1.2 Objectives</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide real AI scoring with traceable feedback and fallback strategies.</li>
    <li>Enable automatic, domain-adaptive question generation to expand the question bank.</li>
    <li>Support multi-role workflows: admin/teacher/student with secure token-based access.</li>
    <li>Ensure stability: unified API responses, robust interceptors, and consistent data types.</li>
    <li>Deliver a demo-ready platform with clear documentation and quick start scripts.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4>1.3 Literature Survey</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>AI-assisted marking systems: strengths in speed and feedback; risks in consistency and bias.</li>
    <li>Item bank management tools: efficient CRUD, batch import/export, metadata management.</li>
    <li>Practice-to-analytics loop: data-driven learning, wrong-question reinforcement.</li>
  </ul>
  <p class="small">
    1.3.1 AI marking best practices and fallback scoring strategies; 1.3.2 Question generation prompts and validation heuristics; 1.3.3 UX for practice flows and transparency
  </p>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h3>2. Project Background and Problem Analysis</h3>
  <h4>2.1 Scope of the problem</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Large cohorts create heavy marking load and slow feedback cycles.</li>
    <li>Limited high-quality question supply for continuous practice.</li>
    <li>Fragmented systems hinder a closed practice–feedback–analytics loop.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4>2.2 Problem Statements and description</h4>
  <p>
    In Hong Kong, rapid curriculum delivery and assessment workloads increase pressure on teachers and students. Manual marking delays learning feedback and makes personalization difficult. Therefore, our project provides an AI-enhanced assessment workflow to shorten cycles and improve learning outcomes. The purpose is to integrate AI scoring and AI question generation into an end-to-end system where users can manage, practice, receive feedback, and analyze performance continuously.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h3>3. Research of Solutions</h3>
  <h4>3.1 Advantages</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>AI scoring accelerates marking and provides explanatory feedback.</li>
    <li>AI question generation expands question supply and supports topic/difficulty control.</li>
    <li>Wrong-question focused practice reinforces weak areas efficiently.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4>3.2 Limitation</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>AI responses can vary; need strict prompts and fallbacks.</li>
    <li>Programming questions require safe sandboxing and resource limits.</li>
    <li>Full analytics and long-term evaluation require more data and iteration.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h3>4. Proposed Solution</h3>
  <h4>4.1 Scope of the proposed solution</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Multi-role platform with subjects, questions, papers, tasks, and logs.</li>
    <li>AI scoring for fill-in-the-blank and programming; rule-based fallback.</li>
    <li>AI question generation by parameters; CSV import/export pipelines.</li>
    <li>Wrong-question drill paper generation and practice detail exports.</li>
  </ul>
  <h4>4.2 System Architecture and roles of hardwares</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Client (Vue 3): UI/UX, routing, state, axios interceptors</li>
    <li>Server (Django): REST API, business logic, AI endpoints, CSV processing</li>
    <li>Database (MySQL): persistent storage</li>
    <li>Optional (Future): Dockerized sandbox runner, Redis/Celery</li>
    <li>Deployment: Linux VM or containerized stack; Nginx reverse proxy</li>
  </ul>
  <h4>4.3 Advantages and drawbacks</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Advantages: Fast feedback loop, closed-loop learning, extendable architecture</li>
    <li>Drawbacks: AI consistency challenges; requires careful ops for sandbox/queue</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h3>5. Requirements</h3>
  <h4>5.1 Roles of Users</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Admin: manage colleges/grades/subjects/users/exams/messages; AI features</li>
    <li>Teacher: manage questions/exams; AI question generation</li>
    <li>Student: practice/tasks/exams; AI scoring access; wrong-question drills</li>
  </ul>
  <h4>5.2 Functional Requirements</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Authentication with token; role-based menus</li>
    <li>Question CRUD; CSV import/export; templates</li>
    <li>Practice paper listing, start/continue/submit; results and exports</li>
    <li>AI scoring and AI question generation endpoints and UI</li>
    <li>Wrong-question paper generation</li>
  </ul>
  <h4>5.3 Non-functional Requirements</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Reliability: clear error handling, interceptors, fallbacks</li>
    <li>Performance: pagination, async requests</li>
    <li>Usability: filterable selects, consistent value types, progress feedback</li>
    <li>Security: token checks, safe file uploads</li>
    <li>Maintainability: modular code, unified API contract</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h3>6. Documentation for Problem Analysis</h3>
  <h4>6.1 Use Case Diagrams of the whole systems</h4>
  <p>Admin: manage users/subjects/questions/exams; import/export; AI generate.<br/>
     Teacher: manage questions/exams; AI generate; review logs.<br/>
     Student: browse papers; start/continue/submit; view results; AI scoring; wrong-question practice.</p>
  <h4>6.2 Fully Dressed Use Cases</h4>
  <p><strong>Scope/System:</strong> Web platform; <strong>Name:</strong> Start a practice; <strong>Primary Actor:</strong> Student.</p>
  <p><strong>Main Success Scenario:</strong> select paper → create/continue log → answer → submit → score & store → result.</p>
  <p><strong>Extensions:</strong> continue unfinished; retry on network error.</p>
  <p><strong>Scope/System:</strong> Web platform; <strong>Name:</strong> Import questions (CSV); <strong>Primary Actor:</strong> Admin/Teacher.</p>
  <p><strong>Main Success Scenario:</strong> upload CSV → validate → store → return success/fail summary.</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
  <h3>7. Documentation for Detailed Design</h3>
  <h4>7.1 Database design (ERD) and metadata</h4>
  <p>Core entities: Users, Projects, Grades, Colleges, Practises, Options, PracticePapers, StudentPracticeLogs, StudentPracticeAnswers, Tasks, StudentTaskLogs, StudentTaskAnswers, Exams, ExamLogs, AnswerLogs, Messages, MessageReads, WrongQuestions, WrongQuestionReviews.</p>
  <p>Key fields example: Practises(id,name,answer,analyse,type(0/1/2/3),project_id,score)</p>
  <h4>7.2 System design</h4>
  <p>Client calls REST APIs via axios; interceptors unify code==0 semantics. Server views: AdminView, StudentPracticeView, AIView. AIUtils: prompt building, model calls, parsing, fallback.</p>
  <h4>7.3 User interface design</h4>
  <p>Dashboards with tags by difficulty/type; filterable lists; progress indicators on AI calls with retry.</p>
</div>

